      "strategyText": "The user strike a pose with a 30 frame startup. Then, fires a projectile that travels >32 studs in 55 frames before despawning. After that, you are left in stun for 25 frames on whiff. If the projectile hit, the user will grab the target and perform a barrage of attacks on them, dealing damage; this give the user self stun for 113f, and give the target stun for 161f, which can lead to many other skills or an M1 in the kit. If the projectile is blocked, the user will get a block endlag of 46f, more than punishable for anyone with half a braincell, so do not use this in neutral.",
      "bulletPoints": [
        "<strong>The Projectile Thingy:</strong> Because the hit detection is tied to a spawned projectile rather than the user's physical body, the move can grab opponents through solid walls, even if the user doesn't move.",
